Class Maze

java.lang.Object
maze.Maze
All Implemented Interfaces:
GraphInterface
public class Maze
extends java.lang.Object
implements GraphInterface
Maze is the class for the mazes.

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors 
    Constructor Description
    Maze​(int height, int width)
    Constructors of a 'Maze object' While created, all the boxes to 'Empty' are initialized to 'Empty' in order to have a maze with the right dimensions, but it will be modified later on.

    • initFromTextFile

      public final void initFromTextFile​(java.lang.String fileName) throws java.io.IOException, MazeReadingException
      Converts the maze (text) of the file into the maze of the class (type Maze).
      Parameters:
      fileName - The path of the file containing the maze, with a text structure.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - if an IO exception occurs.
      MazeReadingException - if the length of a line is different from the width of the maze.

    • lineToMBox

      public java.util.ArrayList<MBox> lineToMBox​(java.lang.String line, int i, java.lang.String fileName) throws MazeReadingException
      Converts a line of text (type String) into a matching line of boxes.
      Parameters:
      line - The string which is to be converted.
      i - The number of the line in the maze.
      fileName - Path of the file which created the parameter line. It has to be a parameter to throw the exception.
      Returns:
      The list of boxes matching the letters of the string line.
      Throws:
      MazeReadingException - If there is a wrong character in the text file
